==English==

====Etymology====
[[cat]] + Middle English ''[[nep]]'', from Old English ''[[nepte]]'', from Latin ''[[nepeta]]''.


===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}
#{{botany}} Any of the about 250 species of flowering plant of the genus ''[[w:Nepeta|Nepeta]]'', family ''[[w:Lamiaceae|Lamiaceae]]'', certain of which are said to have medicinal qualities.
# ''Nepeta cataria'' and ''N. grandiflora'' (and perhaps other species), which are well-known for causing an apparently harmless [[pheromone]]-based intoxication among certain [[cat]]s.
#:''Some cats go bonkers over catnip; others ignore it.''
# Welcomely refreshing or rejuvenating.
#:''Her phone call was catnip to my ears.

====Synonym====
*[[catmint]]

